{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021517\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"487\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-12-at-7.07.07-PM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-12-at-7.07.07-PM.png 730w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-12-at-7.07.07-PM-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021517\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Wednesday, 2/15/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/skill\">Skill</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021517#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>After \u201cDe-loading\u201d our Power Snatch strength program we introduce a new movement to our CrossFit programming, the single arm overhead squat. While the weight might seem light relative to a barbell over head squat there are unique challenges to stabilizing a dumbbell overhead. There is a great deal of mobility and stability involved in this movement. For those who are unable to perform them consider it a goal and accept the challenge of improving your mobility and stability.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Suggested Meal Template:</h2>\n<p>Light</p>\n<h2>Skill:</h2>\n<p>3-Part Pause Snatch (Start, Knee, Hips)</p>\n<p>10x 3 Part Pause Power Snatch<br>\n10x 2 Part Pause Power Snatch (Knee / Hips)<br>\n10x 1 Part Pause Power Snatch (Knee)<br>\n10x Power Snatch (Slow to Knee but no pause)</p>\n<h2>Strength: (20mins)</h2>\n<p><strong>Power Snatch</strong><br>\nWeek 5: \u2013 3@50%, 3@60%, 3@70%, 4\u00d73@80% of (# from Week 1)</p>\n<h2>MetCon: (Cap15)</h2>\n<p><strong>4RFT:</strong><br>\n10 \u201cR\u201d Single Arm OH DB Squat 35/20#<br>\n10 \u201cL\u201d Single Arm OH DB Squat<br>\n12 Strict Chin-up</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
