{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021417\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"664\" height=\"369\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-12-at-6.57.38-PM-blackwhite.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-12-at-6.57.38-PM-blackwhite.png 664w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-12-at-6.57.38-PM-blackwhite-300x167.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 664px) 100vw, 664px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021417\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Tuesday, 2/14/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/stability\">Stability</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021417#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Our muscles and other connective tissues help us move in different directions and planes. You probably don\u2019t think about it but different exercises train our body to move through specific planes. A plane not trained often enough is the frontal plane. This is when we move sideways. The side plank trains us to stabilize the frontal plane rather than move through it.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Suggested Meal Template:</h2>\n<p>Light</p>\n<h2>Stability:</h2>\n<p><strong>Rolling Plank:</strong><br>\n4 Rounds of:<br>\nSide Plank- Plank -Side Plank (20sec each position)<br>\n-rest around 1min</p>\n<h2>MetCon:</h2>\n<p><strong>Chipper Repeats:</strong><br>\n<em>*Score is total reps completed</em><br>\n4 RFR:<br>\nIn 4 minutes complete as many reps as possible:<br>\n25 MB Slams 20/14#<br>\n25 Box Overs 24/20\u2033<br>\n25 MB Cleans<br>\n-rest 1 minute</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
