{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021017\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"926\" height=\"430\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-09-at-3.21.56-PM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-09-at-3.21.56-PM.png 926w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-09-at-3.21.56-PM-300x139.png 300w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-09-at-3.21.56-PM-768x357.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 926px) 100vw, 926px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021017\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Friday, 2/10/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/skill\">Skill</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-021017#comments\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tOne Comment </a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>What better way to kick of a nutrition program than a 20 minute bodyweight workout. This will serve as a test at the beginning of the program that will be retested on the last day of the program. How will a change in body composition improve yo