{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-020217\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"374\" height=\"370\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.20.10-PM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.20.10-PM.png 374w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.20.10-PM-300x297.png 300w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.20.10-PM-50x50.png 50w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.20.10-PM-100x100.png 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 374px) 100vw, 374px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-020217\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Thursday, 2/02/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-020217#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>If \u201cvariance\u201d is an important component of comprehensive training program, today\u2019s MetCon would fulfill that. We pair three unique and completely different movements and train them over a long period of time. Dumbbell Squats are a weightlifting movement that is performed under moderately heavy load. The Farmer\u2019s Walk is a slow and heavy locomotive exercise testing the bodies ability to carry loads and requires a great deal of grip strength. The Bear Crawl is an exercise about mobility and body control.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Strength: (12mins)</h2>\n<p><strong>4 Rounds:</strong><br>\n10 (each) Single Leg RDL<br>\n8 Ring Dips</p>\n<h2>MetCon:</h2>\n<p><strong>\u201cPeaked\u201d</strong><br>\nAMRAP 20<br>\n15 Double DB Front Squat (performed on blue wall) 50/35#<br>\n100\u2019 Bear Crawl (towards leaderboard wall and back 2x)<br>\n200\u2019 Farmer\u2019s Walk (towards leaderboard wall and back 4x) 50/35#</p>\n<p><em>*Every 25\u201d is 1 rep. 1 round of crawls = 4 reps. An entire round = 27 reps.</em></p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
