{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-013117\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"532\" height=\"399\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.16.00-PM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.16.00-PM.png 532w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-29-at-6.16.00-PM-300x225.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-013117\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Tuesday, 1/31/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/skill\">Skill</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-013117#comments\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tOne Comment </a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Our workout will begin in teams. For seven minutes you and your team will be trying to collect as man calories on the rower as possible, each taking turns. As the calories climb on your rower your team will be staying busing performing 3 burpees together for every calories rowed. How you divide the work is up to you.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Team Warm-up:</h2>\n<p>In equaled numbered teams: (3-4 preferably)</p>\n<p><strong>AMRAP 7</strong><br>\nME Cal Row (broken up in anyway)<br>\n<em>*every 10 calories (10,20,30,etc) the athletes not on the rower must complete 3 burpees together.</em><br>\n<em>*athletes can switch at anytime but the team must keep the same order</em></p>\n<h2>Skill: (8mins)</h2>\n<p><strong>Toes to Bar</strong></p>\n<p>Progression video: <a href=\"https://journal.crossfit.com/article/toes-to-bar-progression\" target=\"_blank\">https://journal.crossfit.com/article/toes-to-bar-progression</a></p>\n<h2>Metcon:</h2>\n<p><strong>CrossFit.com 170129</strong><br>\nFor time: (Cap 10)<br>\n15/12/9<br>\nToes to Bar<br>\nWall Balls 20/14#<br>\nThrusters 75/55#</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
