{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-012017\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"661\" height=\"479\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-15-at-6.32.00-PM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-15-at-6.32.00-PM.png 661w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-15-at-6.32.00-PM-300x217.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 661px) 100vw, 661px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-012017\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Friday, 1/20/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-012017#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Our conditioning portion of the workout is what we call a \u201cDouble Death By\u201d. Normally in an Every Minute on the Minute workout you complete as many rounds as possible and once you can not complete a prescribed amount of work within a minute the workout is over. Today\u2019s \u201cDeath By\u201d you will continue on 