{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-011917\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"666\" height=\"328\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-15-at-6.28.48-PM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-15-at-6.28.48-PM.png 666w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-15-at-6.28.48-PM-300x148.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-011917\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Thursday, 1/19/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-011917#comments\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tOne Comment </a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Part of our CrossFit Open preparation includes mastering the Power Snatch. I\u2019m hoping that we can take what we developed between the Hang Snatch program of a couple months ago and our Power Clean program from last month. Be patient, focus on your form, and rely on technique, not strength.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Skill:</h2>\n<p><strong>3-Part Pause Snatch (Start, Knee, Hips)</strong><br>\n10x 3 Part Pause Power Snatch<br>\n10x 2 Part Pause Power Snatch (Knee / Hips)<br>\n10x 1 Part Pause Power Snatch (Knee)<br>\n10x Power Snatch (Slow to Knee but no pause)</p>\n<h2>Strength:</h2>\n<p><strong>5\u00d71 Power Snatch</strong></p>\n<h2>MetCon: (Cap 8)</h2>\n<p><strong>For Time:</strong><br>\n750m Row<br>\n50 DB Snatches 50/35#<br>\n30 Stepback lunges with/ DB 50/35#</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
