the joints so the larger muscles like the deltoids can produce force. They must also have endurance and can handle metabolic stress (aka burning). We will develop this today with some banded shoulder drills.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Warm-up:</h2>\n<p><strong>No Money</strong><br>\n3rnds of:<br>\n10 \u201cno money\u201d palms down<br>\n10 \u201cno money\u201d palms up<br>\n-then<br>\nClapping Penguin<br>\n3x \u201cclapping penguin\u201d palms facing each other<br>\n3x \u201cclapping penguin\u201d palms facing away</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://youtu.be/JbZiAvpN94c\" target=\"_blank\">http://youtu.be/JbZiAvpN94c</a></p>\n<h2>Strength: (12mins)</h2>\n<p><strong>3RM Push Press</strong></p>\n<h2>MetCon: (Cap 15)</h2>\n<p><strong>\u201cCrossFit.com Tuesday 161220\u201d</strong><br>\nFor time:<br>\n10 Thrusters 135/95#<br>\n50 double-unders /150 Singles<br>\n8 Thrusters<br>\n40 double-unders /120 Singles<br>\n6 Thrusters<br>\n30 double-unders /90 Singles<br>\n4 Thrusters<br>\n20 double-unders /60 Singles<br>\n2 Thrusters<br>\n10 double-unders /30 Singles</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
