{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-011317\"><span class=\"post-featured-img\"><img width=\"561\" height=\"512\" src=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-08-at-4.34.57-PM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-08-at-4.34.57-PM.png 561w, http://crossfitonthehill.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Screen-Shot-2017-01-08-at-4.34.57-PM-300x274.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 561px) 100vw, 561px\"></span></a>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-011317\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Friday, 1/13/17\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-011317#comments\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t2 Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Prioritizing the negative or eccentric portion and tempo of the pull-up will improve shoulder/ lat strength and stability. This will increase our ability to perform pull-ups and other overhead pulling movements. This will also allow novices who lack the strength to perform a pull-up to build that necessary strength and control on the negative portion of the movement.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Strength: (10 minutes)</h2>\n<p><strong>Negative Pull-ups:</strong><br>\nRx (Can complete 4 reps of these): 5xME Pull-up w/ 4 second descent<br>\nScaled: 5xME Jumping Pull-up with 4 second descent.</p>\n<h2>MetCon:</h2>\n<p><strong>2 RDS \u2013 AMRAP 6</strong><br>\n20 KB Cleans (2/1.5pd) *Alternating<br>\n10 Front Rack Stepback lunges (left)<br>\n10 Front Rack Stepback lunges (right)<br>\n-Rest 2min<br>\n-Repeat the AMRAP 6</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
