{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-110216\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Wednesday, 11/02/16\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-110216#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>It seems like most did very well with the Back Squat Strength Program. Today we will begin the Front Squat Strength Program. Compared to the Back Squat the Front Squat is a bit more quad dominant, requires more anterior core strength and incorporates a much more vertical torso throughout the movement. I also find it more transferrable to more CrossFit exercises.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Warm-up:</h2>\n<p>1min Baby Squat<br>\n2xGreen Mile<br>\n20 Wall Squat</p>\n<h2>Strength: (20mins)</h2>\n<p><strong>Week 1: Front Squat</strong><br>\n3\u00d78 w/ 2 sec Pause in bottom</p>\n<h2>MetCon:</h2>\n<p><strong>AMRAP 10</strong><br>\n10 STOH 95/65#<br>\n20 Barbell Stepback Lunges (front rack)<br>\n30 Lateral Bar Hopes (off 2 feet, land 2 feet)</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
