{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-103116\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Monday, 10/31/16\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-103116#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>It\u2019s Halloween so it feels right to perform a \u201cDeath By\u201d workout. If you can not complete the desired amount of repetitions of EITHER movement in the assigned minute you will not longer be able to continue. This will be a great test of strength and conditioning to start the week.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Power Clean</h2>\n<p><strong>Warm-up:</strong><br>\n5x 3 Part Pause Clean ( 2\u201d, Knee, Thigh)<br>\n5x 2 Part Pause Clean (2\u201d, Knee)<br>\n5x 1 Part Pause Clean (Knee)</p>\n<p><strong>Strength:</strong><br>\nWeek 1: 5\u00d71 AHAP Power Clean<br>\n<em>*all at the same weight)</em><br>\n<em>*no starfishes</em><br>\n<em>*Record number</em></p>\n<h2>Metcon: EMOTM \u2013 Death by (Cap 20 minutes)</h2>\n<p><strong>\u201cDouble Jeopardy\u201d</strong><br>\n<strong>Odd Minutes:</strong><br>\n1 Power Clean (155/105#) (+1 rep)</p>\n<p><strong>Even Minutes:</strong><br>\n10 Wall Balls (20/14#)(+1 rep)</p>\n<p>Penalty: 30sec plank for the beginning of each minute</p>\n<p>*Athlete can \u201cdie\u201d during either exercise which means they are done.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
