{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-102016\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Thursday, 10/20/16\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-102016#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>After finalizing our Back Squat program it\u2019s a good idea to revert back to unilateral leg strengthening exercises to lessen any compensations that were exacerbated during bilateral exercises (squatting). If you felt like you were hitting a wall with your squats reverting back to unilateral movements can often help an athlete bust through plateaus.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Strength:</h2>\n<p>4\u00d720 Walking Double KB Front Rack Lunges </p>\n<p><iframe width=\"1080\" height=\"608\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/_Jz-jOStWhw?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<h2>AMRAP 17</h2>\n<p><strong>\u201cDonkey Kong\u201d</strong><br>\n3 Deadlifts 315/235#<br>\n3 Wall Climbs<br>\n20 MB Slams 20/14#</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
