{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-090516\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Tuesday, 9/5/16\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/skill\">Skill</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-090516#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>We have designed a warm-up and set of drills that we will be practicing to master the Hang Snatch over the next 6 months. Once a week we will be performing these drills and applying it to improve strength, coordination and speed of the Snatch. Be patient and pay attention to detail when learning such a technical move.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Skill</h2>\n<p><strong>Hang Snatch:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Warm-up w/ PVC:</strong><br>\n<em>*Each one starts in the tall hang position, hook grip, vertical torso, knees bent.</em><br>\n10x Drive and Shrug<br>\n10x Drive, Shrug, High Elbow Pull (bar stays against the body)<br>\n10x (Hang Muscle Snatch) Drive, Shrug, High Elbow Pull, Turnover w/ Punch Out (No re-bend of the knee)<br>\n10x Hang Power Snatch ( Fast Feet, Knees Re-bend)</p>\n<p><em>*Repeat Hang Power Snatch 3\u00d75 with barbell before loading.</em></p>\n<h2>Strength: (15-20mins)</h2>\n<p><strong>Hang Snatch \u2013 Week 1:</strong><br>\n5\u00d71 AHAP all at the same weight. Record Weight.</p>\n<h2>MetCon: (Cap 15)</h2>\n<p><strong>For time: </strong><br>\nDescending Ladder from (10-1) of:<br>\nDeadlifts 225/155#<br>\nToes to Bar</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
