{"all": "<div class=\"content-inner\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"article-content-wrap\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-header\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"title\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-090216\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWOD for Friday, 9/2/16\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t </a> \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</h2>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"meta-author\"><span>By</span> <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/author/admin\" title=\"Posts by CrossFit on the Hill\" rel=\"author\">CrossFit on the Hill</a></span> <span class=\"meta-category\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/strength-programming\">Strength Programming</a>, <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/category/wod\">WOD</a></span> <span class=\"meta-comment-count\">| <a href=\"http://crossfitonthehill.com/wod/wod-090216#respond\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNo Comments</a></span>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--/post-header-->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>No matter the division you might be required to perform Double Unders at this years In-House Throwdown in October. If this isn\u2019t a skill you\u2019ve mastered you will want to keep practicing. An easy way to start is performing 2 minutes of as many double unders as possible every couple of days. That will also serve as our Fitness Test today.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Skill:</h2>\n<p><strong>Double Unders</strong></p>\n<h2>Fitness Test:</h2>\n<p><strong>2min ME Double Unders</strong></p>\n<h2>MetCon:</h2>\n<p><em>*Adaptation of Crossfit.com Monday 160822</em></p>\n<p><strong>From 0:00-3:00, perform 3 rounds of:</strong><br>\n3 pull-ups<br>\n6 push-ups<br>\n9 squats</p>\n<p><strong>From 3:00-6:00, perform 3 rounds of:</strong><br>\n4 pull-ups<br>\n8 push-ups<br>\n12 squats</p>\n<p><strong>From 6:00-9:00, perform 3 rounds of:</strong><br>\n5 pull-ups<br>\n10 push-ups<br>\n15 squats</p>\n<p><strong>From 9:00-12:00, perform 3 rounds of:</strong><br>\n6 pull-ups<br>\n12 push-ups<br>\n18 squats</p>\n<p><strong>From 12:00-15:00, perform 3 Rounds of:</strong><br>\n9 pull-ups<br>\n15 push-ups<br>\n21 squats</p>\n<p><em>*Rest after completing reps if time allows</em><br>\n<em>*Athletes work for the entire 15 mins regardless</em><br>\n<em>*Score as an AMRAP unless you complete the entire ladder</em></p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div><!--article-content-wrap-->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t   \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>"}
